name: italian seafood stew

food.name: tomato sauces pastes and purees no salt added

servings.unit: lb (with shell), yield after shell removed

serving.unit: lb (with shell), yield after shell removed

food.name: fish sea bass mixed species raw

instructions:
1. Heat olive oil in a large pot. 

2. Slice, fennel, celery and onion, and add to hot oil. 

3. Add oregano and red pepper flakes. Cook over medium-high heat and stir frequently until vegetables are tender.

4. Reduce heat to low and add in squid; stir occasionally for another 15 minutes.

5. Add in wine and bring to a boil over medium-high heat. Cook until the wine is evaporated.

6. Add in tomato puree and lemon zest. Cook until thickened.

7. Add in water and clam juice; bring to a boil.

8. Add in clams and cook until shells open.

9. Add in bass and cook through.

10. Garnish with fresh parsley.
